ciscoSsgMIB.name: ciscoSsgMIB

revisions.description: Imported Unsigned32 from SNMPv2-SMI instead of CISCO-TC.
Added new objects for Transparent Auto-Logon feature.
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoSsgMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-ssg@cisco.com
ciscoSsgMIB.description: The MIB Module manages Service Selection Gateway(SSG) devices. Service Selection Gateway(SSG) is a switching solution for service providers who offer intranet,extranet, and Internet connections to subscribers using broadband access technology such as digital subscriber lines, cable modems, or wireless to allow simultaneous access to network services. Acronyms and terms: SSD Service Selection Dashboard SESM Subscriber Edge Service Manager GGSN Gateway GPRS Support Node APN Access Point Name

cssgCfgSsgEnabled.name: cssgCfgSsgEnabled
cssgCfgSsgEnabled.description: An indication of whether SSG Service is enabled.

cssgCfgAutoDomainMode.name: cssgCfgAutoDomainMode
cssgCfgAutoDomainMode.description: An indication of whether Auto-Domain feature is enabled. This feature allows a user to be automatically connected to a service based on the APN or structured username.

cssgCfgLocalForwardingEnabled.name: cssgCfgLocalForwardingEnabled
cssgCfgLocalForwardingEnabled.description: An indication of whether Local Forwarding is enabled. This feature enables SSG to forward packets locally between connected subscribers.

cssgCfgAutoLogOffMode.name: cssgCfgAutoLogOffMode
cssgCfgAutoLogOffMode.description: An indication of whether Auto Logoff feature is enabled. This feature enables SSG to initiate logoff if connectivity to a host is lost. Connectivity to a host is checked using ARP or ICMP ping mechanisms.

cssgCfgRadiusProxyEnabled.name: cssgCfgRadiusProxyEnabled
cssgCfgRadiusProxyEnabled.description: An indication of whether Radius-Proxy feature is enabled. This feature allows SSG to act as a generic Radius Proxy for non-SSD clients such as GGSN.

cssgCfgTcpRedirectEnabled.name: cssgCfgTcpRedirectEnabled
cssgCfgTcpRedirectEnabled.description: An indication of whether TCP redirect is enabled. This feature redirects certain TCP packets to captive portals.

cssgCfgAutoDomainNatEnabled.name: cssgCfgAutoDomainNatEnabled
cssgCfgAutoDomainNatEnabled.description: An indication of whether NAT(Network Address Translation) is enabled for autodomain users. This feature determines whether the subscriber gets the autodomain service assigned IP Address.

cssgCfgPortBundleHostKeyEnabled.name: cssgCfgPortBundleHostKeyEnabled
cssgCfgPortBundleHostKeyEnabled.description: An indication of whether PortBundle-Host Key feature is enabled. This feature enables SESM to identify subscribers based on the PortBundle(combination of IP Address, and a range of ports) assigned by the SSG.

cssgCfgTransPassThroughEnabled.name: cssgCfgTransPassThroughEnabled
cssgCfgTransPassThroughEnabled.description: An indication of whether Transparent pass through feature is enabled. This feature allows an unauthenticated subscriber traffic to be routed through SSG in either direction.

cssgCfgAutoLogOffInterval.name: cssgCfgAutoLogOffInterval
cssgCfgAutoLogOffInterval.description: The time-interval at which connectivity to a host is checked. If the host is not reachable, SSG logs off the host if auto-logff feature is enabled.

cssgCfgAutoLogOffIcmpRetries.name: cssgCfgAutoLogOffIcmpRetries
cssgCfgAutoLogOffIcmpRetries.description: The number of ICMP ping retries SSG does to check connectivity to a host.

cssgCfgMaxServicesPerUser.name: cssgCfgMaxServicesPerUser
cssgCfgMaxServicesPerUser.description: The maximum number of services allowed per user.

cssgCfgAccountingEnabled.name: cssgCfgAccountingEnabled
cssgCfgAccountingEnabled.description: An indication of whether Acccounting is enabled in SSG. If enabled, SSG generates Accounting Records and sends to AAA Server.

cssgCfgDefaultNetworkType.name: cssgCfgDefaultNetworkType
cssgCfgDefaultNetworkType.description: A value that represents the type of the IP Address stored in the object cssgCfgDefaultNetwork.

cssgCfgDefaultNetwork.name: cssgCfgDefaultNetwork
cssgCfgDefaultNetwork.description: The IP Address or subnet that users will be able to access without authentication. This is the address where the Cisco SSD/SESM resides.

cssgCfgRadiusAuthenPort.name: cssgCfgRadiusAuthenPort
cssgCfgRadiusAuthenPort.description: The port on which SSG receives access request packets from Radius clients.

cssgCfgRadiusAccountingPort.name: cssgCfgRadiusAccountingPort
cssgCfgRadiusAccountingPort.description: The port on which SSG receives accounting packets from Radius clients.

cssgCfgRadiusFwdAcctPktsEnabled.name: cssgCfgRadiusFwdAcctPktsEnabled
cssgCfgRadiusFwdAcctPktsEnabled.description: An indication of whether SSG forwards Accounting Packets received from Radius Clients to AAA Server.

cssgCfgAccountingInterval.name: cssgCfgAccountingInterval
cssgCfgAccountingInterval.description: The interval at which Accounting records are sent to AAA Server.

cssgCfgTCPRedirGrpForUnAuthUsers.description: The TCP Redirect Group to which Unauthenticated users are directed.

cssgCfgTCPRedirGrpForUnAuthServ.description: The TCP Redirect Group to which unauthorized service access users are directed.

cssgCfgRadiusClntRbtNotifEnabled.description: An indication of whether SSG generates notification if a Radius Client reboots.

cssgCfgAAAServerDownNotifEnabled.name: cssgCfgAAAServerDownNotifEnabled
cssgCfgAAAServerDownNotifEnabled.description: An indication of whether SSG generates notification if connectivity to AAA is lost or if it goes down.

cssgCfgTalEnabled.name: cssgCfgTalEnabled
cssgCfgTalEnabled.description: An indication of whether Transparent Auto Logon feature is enabled on SSG.

cssgServiceTable.name: cssgServiceTable
cssgServiceTable.description: A list of SSG Services which subscribers have logged onto. A Service entry in this table is transient data and gets removed when the last subscriber using this Service logs off.

cssgServiceName.name: cssgServiceName
cssgServiceName.description: The name of the service profile.

cssgServiceMode.name: cssgServiceMode
cssgServiceMode.description: An optional attribute which defines whether the user is able to log in to a service while simultaneously connected to other services (concurrent) or cannot access any other services while using this service (sequential). The default is concurrent.

cssgServiceType.name: cssgServiceType
cssgServiceType.description: This attribute indicates the type of service. pass-through - Indicates that the user authentication is not done during logon to this service. This is the default. tunnel - Indicates that this is a L2TP tunneled service. proxy - Indicates that the SSG performs user authentication during logon to this service.

cssgServiceIdleTimeout.name: cssgServiceIdleTimeout
cssgServiceIdleTimeout.description: The idle timeout of a session in seconds. A value of 0 indicates that there is no timeout.

cssgServiceSessionTimeout.name: cssgServiceSessionTimeout
cssgServiceSessionTimeout.description: The maximum length of a session in seconds. A value of 0 indicates that there is no timeout.

cssgServiceActiveSessions.name: cssgServiceActiveSessions
cssgServiceActiveSessions.description: The active number of connections to this service.

cssgTalWaitingForAuthUsers.name: cssgTalWaitingForAuthUsers
cssgTalWaitingForAuthUsers.description: The number of currently existing users waiting for authorization.

cssgTalUnidentifiedUsers.name: cssgTalUnidentifiedUsers
cssgTalUnidentifiedUsers.description: The number of currently existing unidentified users. These are users for which there was no response received from AAA and hence it is not clear if they are valid users.

cssgTalSuspectUsers.name: cssgTalSuspectUsers
cssgTalSuspectUsers.description: The number of currently existing Suspect Users.

cssgTalPassthroughUsers.name: cssgTalPassthroughUsers
cssgTalPassthroughUsers.description: The number of currently existing transparent pass-through users.

cssgTalMaxAuthRate.name: cssgTalMaxAuthRate
cssgTalMaxAuthRate.description: Maximum rate of authorization requests per second. At a given time, the maximum rate of authorization requests will overwrite the previous value.

cssgTalMaxAuthRateTimestamp.name: cssgTalMaxAuthRateTimestamp
cssgTalMaxAuthRateTimestamp.description: This is the local time on the SSG when the Maximum rate of authorization requests per second, indicated by cssgTalMaxAuthRate, was recorded.

cssgTalMinAuthRate.name: cssgTalMinAuthRate
cssgTalMinAuthRate.description: Minimum rate of authorization requests per second. At a given time, the minimum rate of authorization requests will overwrite the previous value.

cssgTalMinAuthRateTimestamp.name: cssgTalMinAuthRateTimestamp
cssgTalMinAuthRateTimestamp.description: This is the local time on the SSG when the Minimum rate of authorization requests per second, indicated by cssgTalMinAuthRate, was recorded.

cssgTalCurrentAuthRate.name: cssgTalCurrentAuthRate
cssgTalCurrentAuthRate.description: The last recorded rate of authorization requests per second, on SSG.

cssgTalCurrentAuthRateTimestamp.name: cssgTalCurrentAuthRateTimestamp
cssgTalCurrentAuthRateTimestamp.description: This is the local time on the SSG when cssgTalCurrentAuthRate, was recorded.

cssgTalResetAuthRates.name: cssgTalResetAuthRates
cssgTalResetAuthRates.description: Setting this variable to 'reset' indicates that the Minimum and Maximum rates of authorization would be reset to the last recorded rate of authorization requests per second. Setting it to 'unknown' will not result in any changes. An snmp-get on this value will always return 'unknown'.

cssgTalMaxPendingAuthReqs.name: cssgTalMaxPendingAuthReqs
cssgTalMaxPendingAuthReqs.description: The maximum number of outstanding TAL authorization requests allowed on SSG. If the number of authorization requests goes beyond this value, SSG does a SYS log message and any packets received that would result in SSG sending a new radius request will be dropped at the CEF path itself. When this value is set, it will be applicable from that point onwards. If the number of existing requests exceeds the new values, these requests will not be discarded.

cssgTalMaxAuthReqsRate.name: cssgTalMaxAuthReqsRate
cssgTalMaxAuthReqsRate.description: The maximum number of authorization requests per second allowed on SSG. If this value is set, SSG throttles the authorization requests sent per second as per this value.

cssgTalDropPakDuringAuthorization.name: cssgTalDropPakDuringAuthorization
cssgTalDropPakDuringAuthorization.description: The value 'true' indicates that any packets that are received from the user during user authorization would be dropped. The value 'false' indicates that the packets will not be dropped.

cssgTalUnidentifiedUserAllowTraff.name: cssgTalUnidentifiedUserAllowTraff
cssgTalUnidentifiedUserAllowTraff.description: The value 'true' indicates that traffic from/to unidentified users would be allowed. A value of 'false' indicates that traffic from/to unidentified users will not be allowed.

cssgTalMaxSuspectUsers.name: cssgTalMaxSuspectUsers
cssgTalMaxSuspectUsers.description: The maximum number of suspect users allowed.

cssgTalSuspectUserTimeout.name: cssgTalSuspectUserTimeout
cssgTalSuspectUserTimeout.description: The timeout value for a suspect user in minutes. If a packet is received for a suspect user, then packets from/to this user will be dropped/tcp-redirected, until a value of cssgTalSuspectUserTimeout is reached. After this timeout, any new traffic received by SSG from the suspect user will trigger the TAL procedure all over again.

cssgTalUnidentifiedUserTimeout.name: cssgTalUnidentifiedUserTimeout
cssgTalUnidentifiedUserTimeout.description: The timeout value for an unidentified user in minutes. After this time expiry, authorization will be done again when a packet is received from this user.
